                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>The AbbVie Foundation and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.care.org/&quot; title=&quot;https://www.care.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>CARE&lt;/a>, in partnership with &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.msm.edu/&quot; title=&quot;https://www.msm.edu/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Morehouse School of Medicine&lt;/a>, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.lyft.com/&quot; title=&quot;https://www.lyft.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Lyft&lt;/a> and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.acfb.org/&quot; title=&quot;https://www.acfb.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Atlanta Community Food Bank&lt;/a>, are piloting an innovative model of care that provides complete, connected support and services to pregnant people in underserved Atlanta communities — with the aim of removing barriers and improving maternal health outcomes. &amp;nbsp;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Insights from this two-year pilot will help us scale solutions to address other critical health challenges in communities across the U.S. and beyond.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
